Files containing the handler implementations for book_api:

- app/api/v1/book.py

Explanation:
- I inspected the project tree and opened app/api/v1/book.py. That file defines book_api = Blueprint("book", __name__) and all route handlers for the /book blueprint.
- The handlers defined there are: get_book (GET /<int:id>), get_books (GET /), search (GET /search), create_book (POST /), update_book (PUT /<int:id>), and delete_book (DELETE /<int:id>).
- app/api/v1/__init__.py registers this blueprint at the URL prefix /book, so the implementations in app/api/v1/book.py are the handlers used for the /book endpoints.
